description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a new service manager to work within our clinical directorate management teams. This is a key position focusing on Cardiology and Neurology within the Medicine and Urgent Care division.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your role will be to provide operational service management and leadership to support the directorate in achieving its performance objectives. Working closely with clinicians, nurses, managers and admin teams, you will ensure achievement against financial, activity and access targets, and in line with our commitment to providing world class care. You will have excellent staff management skills, experience of managing change, and the ability to negotiate with stakeholders at all levels.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post will be of interest to those who wish to pursue a career in hospital management and would like to gain more experience in a busy directorate with a wide variety of challenges. You will need to have excellent communication skills and be able to demonstrate that you can lead and motivate a team. You will need to liaise with patients, clinicians and managers within the Trust and at external organisations. Time management skills are also essential as you will need to balance the demands of a very busy workload. If you believe you have the skills, enthusiasm and ambition to join our team, we would love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It’s a great time to join our team of progressive clinicians and managers at this highly successful NHS Foundation Trust at a time of change, expansion and service transformation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Josie Mulvey&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Assistant operational Manager Cardiology / Neurology&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address:Josephine.mulvey@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 0208 2165774&lt;/p&gt;
